<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-AkGHYbwy4lksGw1DJDjNjA" name="asset_fit_gap_analysis,_t8NJEFa9Ed6MCpkuB85p5g" guid="-AkGHYbwy4lksGw1DJDjNjA" changeDate="2009-08-26T07:01:33.031-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>An existing asset seldom is a perfect fit for all the requirements of a specific service.&amp;nbsp; Perhaps there is a&#xD;
functional mis-match,&amp;nbsp;the ServiceInterface signature and the asset's operations signature do not align perfectly, or&#xD;
the asset does not satisfy non-functional requirements.&amp;nbsp; An asset fit gap analysis documents the nature of these&#xD;
mis-matches and supports making a decision regarding whether the asset will be used to realize a given service.</mainDescription>
  <purpose>To&amp;nbsp;document (1) the degree to which an as-is asset (in the context of a SOA engagement, this usually is some running&#xD;
software) is fit for a candidate purpose and (2)&amp;nbsp;goodness-of-fit gaps.</purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>This is a key artifact supporting existing asset analysis.&amp;nbsp; Without this, it is very difficult to make reasoned&#xD;
decisions regarding whether it is feasible and desirable to realize a given service&amp;nbsp;using a specific existing asset.</impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>Very few reasons exist for not creating an asset fit gap analysis artifact, other than the fact that all services are to be&#xD;
original implementations.</reasonsForNotNeeding>
  <representation>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This usually will be a textual artifact, or a combined textual/graphic artifact.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Useful graphics include diagrams which show services and the assets which are candidates for implementations, candidate&#xD;
    assets grouped by&amp;nbsp;the functional area they support, etc.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Textual information that is gathered can include the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Name and description of the asset&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Business process or service it is being considered for use in&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Gap(s) description&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Assessed degree and severity of gap&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Candidate approach on addressing any gaps&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></representation>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
